OL,3,CResidents concerned about council
OL,4,Cproposals to close public toilets
OL,6,FPeople living and travelling to
OL,7,FLlangollen are concerned about council
OL,8,Fproposals to close public toilets in
OL,9,Fthe town.
OL,11,FThe local authority runs the toilets
OL,12,Fin Llangollen but it has no legal
OL,13,Fobligation. So they could get rid of
OL,14,Fthe toilets to save money.
OL,16,FRetired General Practitioner and
OL,17,FLlangollen resident Dr Rhys Davies
OL,18,Fsays there is a 'moral obligation' to
OL,19,Fprovide public conveniences.
