OL,3,CResidents concerned about council
OL,4,Cproposals to close public toilets
OL,6,F"We know finances are tight, but
OL,7,Fcouncils could be more innovative in
OL,8,Ftheir approach to public toilet
OL,9,Fprovision by opening public buildings
OL,10,Ffor people to use or working more
OL,11,Fclosely with local businesses to
OL,12,Fincrease the provision of public
OL,13,Ftoilets."
OL,15,FDenbighshire County Council say they,
OL,16,Flike many local authorities are facing
OL,17,Fsignificant challenges.
